benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Remove tags from account

covered: Valid Deletion: Scenarios demonstrate successful deletion of tags (single, multiple, and all when no tagDef is provided).
Header/Authorization coverage: Tests verify required X-Killbill-CreatedBy header and correct error handling for missing/invalid authentication (TC09, TC15).
Query Parameters handling: Tests cover single/multiple/none/empty-array tagDef values and extra/unexpected parameters (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC11, TC13, TC18, TC20).

Domain validation and error cases: Tests verify invalid accountId (TC07), non-existent account (TC06), invalid tagDef (TC08), malformed tagDef (TC14), and domain constraint (AUTO_PAY_OFF with no default payment method, TC10).
Resilience: Tests simulate service unavailability (TC12) and transient network failure with retry (TC16).
Performance/Concurrency: Tests cover concurrent deletions (TC17) and large tagDef sets (TC13).
Regression/Compatibility: Tests ensure behavior with mixed valid/invalid tagDefs (TC18) and backwards compatibility with omitted optional headers (TC19).
gaps: Soft delete semantics not covered (whether deletions are hard vs soft deletes).
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching behavior (ETag/Cache-Control headers) is not tested.
Not-found semantics: current tests use 400 for non-existent accounts; consider adding 404 Not Found test for not-found resources.
Atomicity nuances: no explicit test for partial deletion when only part of the provided tagDefs are deleted in the same request beyond the regression case.
recommendations: Add 404 Not Found test for non-existent accounts to align with RESTful semantics.
Add explicit soft delete semantics verification to determine whether deletions are hard or soft.
Introduce rate limiting and throttling tests to ensure the API handles bursts gracefully.
Add tests for caching semantics (ETag/Cache-Control) to verify caching behavior.
Extend tests to cover edge-case partial deletions with mixed valid/invalid tagDefs beyond current regression coverage.
Tighten header validation tests to include invalid CreatedBy values and ensure consistent 400/401 responses.
